JOHHANESBURG - South African Airways chairperson, Dudu Myeni's stay at the airline is illegal in terms of the Companies Act. That's according to the Companies and Intellectual Property Commission.It s told Treasury that Myeni has served three consecutive terms, making her ineligible for any further extensions.READ: SAA's Myeni under fireBusiness Day is reporting the CIPC informed the finance minister no notice had been filed, telling the regulator that Myeni's contract had been extended.SAA had 10 working days to do so.Her board contract ended at the end of August and Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba extended it until 3 November.eNCA